<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.classification_select">
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Type: complete_membership_select 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.complete_membership_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.complete_membership_select">
A <b>complete_membership_select</b> is a thing that is specified to be one of the members of an explicitly enumerated set.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: class  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.class">
<p>A <b>class</b> is a set.</p>

<note number="1"> The term 'set' is defined in clause 3.3. In this part of ISO 10303, 'set' and 'class' are synonyms.</note>

<note number="2"><p>The meaning of this entity is identical to:</p>
<ul><li>
the entity class defined in ISO 10303-214; and </li><li>
the entity class defined in ISO 15926-2. </li></ul></note>
<note number="3"> A class can consist of all things with a particular set of properties. Hence information about the consequences of possessing the set of properties can be assigned to the class.
If a thing is classified as being a member of such a class, then a set of properties possessed by the thing can be deduced.</note>
<note number="4">This entity may be instantiated as a compound instance involving another entity from ISO 10303.</note>
<note number="5">The distinction between a <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class_by_extension"/>

 and a <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class_by_intension"/>

 can be imprecise. For example, the set of items produced by a particular production run could be regarded as either. The entity type class is not specified as abstract, so an application protocol or application module can decide to ignore the distinction.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: class_by_extension  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class_by_extension"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.class_by_extension">
A <b>class_by_extension</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/>

 that is defined by enumerating all the members.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: class_by_intension  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class_by_intension"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.class_by_intension">
A <b>class_by_intension</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/>

 that is defined by means of criteria. A thing is a member of the set if it satisfies all the criteria.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: classification  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.classification"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.classification">
<p>A <b>classification</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.classification_assignment"/>

that is a relationship  between:</p> 
<ul><li>
set S;</li><li> 
thing x, 
</li></ul>
<p>that indicates thing x is a member of set S.</p>

<note>The meaning of this entity is identical to the entity classification defined in ISO 15926-2.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: classification  Attribute: classified 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.classification.classified"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.classification.classified">
the member of the <b>classifier</b>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: classification  Attribute: classifier 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.classification.classifier"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.classification.classifier">
the <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/>

 that has the <b>classified</b> as a member.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: complete_membership  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.complete_membership"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.complete_membership">
<p>A <b>complete_membership</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.classification_assignment"/>

that is a relationship  between:</p> 
<ul><li>
set S; and</li><li>
enumerated things xi, </li></ul>
<p>that indicates set S contains each of the things xi and nothing else.</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: complete_membership  Attribute: members 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.complete_membership.members"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.complete_membership.members">
<p>the elements of the <b>containing_set</b>.</p>
<note>The containing set can be specified to be empty.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Entity: complete_membership  Attribute: containing_set 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.complete_membership.containing_set"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.complete_membership.containing_set">
the <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/>

 that contains the members and nothing else.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: classification_schema  Subtype constraint: classification_or_complete_membership  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.classification_or_complete_membership"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="classification_schema.classification_or_complete_membership">
A <b>classification_or_complete_membership</b>  specifies that a <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.classification_assignment"/>

 shall either specify some of the members of a class without an assertion of completeness, or all of the members of a class with an assertion of completeness.</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
